Error: New Minecraft Server Error: "Connection Refused: No Further Information."

Solution: 1. Check your internet connection. This error might occur due to connectivity issues or the server may be down.
2. Verify that your Minecraft client is up-to-date. This is important when attempting to connect to any Minecraft server.
3. Make sure that you are using the correct server address or IP. Verify the server information by confirming with the server owner or a friend who has connected to the same server.
